# lib/web/font_adv.ad — hambrowse-side per-GLYPH advance override (round 16).
#
# WHY: hambrowse embeds the DejaVu faces but the Chromium reference renders with
# Liberation Sans (metric-compatible with Arial). lib/font_ttf.ad width-matches
# DejaVu to Liberation with a SINGLE per-face scale (877/1000 sans, 839 bold) —
# the corpus-mean Liberation/DejaVu advance ratio. That mean is right on mixed
# prose but WRONG per glyph class: measured vs `chromium` at 16px a 36-char caps
# run is 47px too NARROW (hb over-condenses wide caps) while a 35-char narrow run
# (i l 1 j t . , ; :) is 23px too WIDE (hb under-condenses thin glyphs). The
# error cancels on average text but compounds on caps/narrow-heavy runs.
#
# FIX (this module): replace the uniform scale with the ACTUAL Liberation Sans
# per-glyph advance, measured directly from the Chromium reference via the
# canvas 2D `measureText` API (`ctx.font='16px sans-serif'`, run/50 to cancel
# side bearings). Stored below as font-units at DejaVu's 2048 upm so it drops
# straight into font_ttf_fu_to_px / the fu-accumulation path with NO change to
# font_ttf.ad (DE-SHARED, off-limits). Both the LAYOUT measure hook and the
# PIXEL paint (lib/htmlpaint.ad) consult this same table, so measure == paint
# (no phantom gaps — cf. round 15). Only FACE_TT_SANS / FACE_TT_SANS_BOLD are
# overridden (the prose faces); serif/mono keep font_ttf's identity metric, and
# a codepoint outside ASCII 32..126 falls back to font_ttf (returns -1 here).
#
# DE-UNCHANGED: this file lives under lib/web/ and is imported only by
# lib/htmlpaint.ad, which only the hambrowse binaries import — no DE binary
# (hamde/hamUI/hampanel/hamdesktop) reaches lib/web or lib/htmlpaint. font_ttf.ad
# is untouched.

FA_UPM: int64 = 2048            # DejaVu unitsPerEm (matches ft_upm default)
FA_LO:  int32 = 32             # first covered codepoint (space)
FA_HI:  int32 = 126            # last covered codepoint (~)

fa_sans: Array[95, int64]      # Liberation Sans   advance, fu @2048upm, cp32..126
fa_bold: Array[95, int64]      # Liberation Sans Bold advance, fu @2048upm
fa_ready: int32 = 0

def _fa_init():
    if fa_ready != 0:
        return
    fa_sans[0] = 569
    fa_sans[1] = 569
    fa_sans[2] = 727
    fa_sans[3] = 1139
    fa_sans[4] = 1139
